I am assistant professor (_Maître de conférences_) at the [university of Lille 1][ustl] ([UFR IEEA][ieea]) since september 2008.

I teach at [Telecom Lille 1][telecom],
and research at [Inria][] within the [RMoD project-team][rmod].

I'm a co-author of the book [Squeak by Example][sbe].

##### Education
I received an engineering degree in computer science from [Insa][] in 2001, and obtained my Ph.D in 2005 from the [university of Rennes 1][rennes1], France; my advisor was [Pr. Jean-Marc Jézéquel][jmj]. After a couple post-docs, I was recruited in Lille; for the complete plot twists, feel free to consult my [bio](bio.html).

